---

To add a new tool to a conversation in Experiment, you can paste a JSON schema into the chat input. Here's how to do it:

1. Create your tool schema in either OpenAI/Mistral format or Anthropic format
2. Paste it into the chat input when the role is set to "tool"

Here's an example of a tool in OpenAI/Mistral format:

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "type": "function",
  "function": {
    "name": "get_stock_price",
    "description": "Get the current stock price for a given ticker symbol",
    "parameters": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "ticker": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "The stock ticker symbol, e.g. AAPL for Apple Inc."
        }
      },
      "required": ["ticker"]
    }
  }
}
```

And here's the same tool in Anthropic format:

```json
{
  "name": "get_stock_price",
  "description": "Get the current stock price for a given ticker symbol",
  "input_schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "ticker": {
        "type": "string",
        "description": "The stock ticker symbol, e.g. AAPL for Apple Inc."
      }
    },
    "required": ["ticker"]
  }
}
```

The application will automatically detect and parse these schemas, then add them to your conversation as tool messages. When you run the experiment, the LLM will have access to these tools and can use them in its responses.
